":"Supports recording safeguarding consideration and clinician-confirmed assessment, plan, communication and follow-up before discharge after self-harm."}]},{"source_resolves":true,"source_id":"rcem-mental-health-toolkit-2023","title":"Mental Health in Emergency Departments: A toolkit for improving care","issuing_organisation":"Royal College of Emergency Medicine","official_url":"https://rcem.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Mental_Health_Toolkit_April_2023_v1.pdf","jurisdiction":"United Kingdom emergency medicine; UAE law and pathways govern local use","sections":[{"section_id":"rcem-mental-health-2023-triage-proforma","heading":"Mental Health Triage and Initial Assessment","locator":"PDF pages 7–8","evidence_summary":"Supports documenting current presenting state, agitation, immediate safety, safeguarding, willingness to accept care, observation level and care-plan status; it explicitly warns triage is not a future-risk prediction tool."}]}],"evidence_links":[{"evidence_item_id":"ed-self-harm-documentation-prompts--nice-ng225-self-harm-psychosocial-assessment","source_id":"nice-self-harm-ng225-2022","source_section_id":"nice-ng225-self-harm-psychosocial-assessment","direct_relationship":"The exact NICE psychosocial-assessment section supports documenting onset or context, severity or impact, associated symptoms, relevant negatives, the person’s concerns or goals and clinician risk context without using a prediction score.","paraphrased_evidence_summary":"Supports recording the person’s needs, concerns, strengths, vulnerabilities, context and clinician-performed psychosocial assessment without using a prediction score.","content_mapping_status":"reviewed_not_mapped_to_legacy_content","candidate_status":"review_only_not_approved","source_resolves":true},{"evidence_item_id":"ed-self-harm-documentation-prompts--nice-ng225-self-harm-ed-assessment","source_id":"nice-self-harm-ng225-2022","source_section_id":"nice-ng225-self-harm-ed-assessment","direct_relationship":"The